<item>
            <title>[LU-13399] too many namespace LFSCK repair the shard messages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13399</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LFSCK is too noisy about (not) repairing sharded dirs even there was nothing to repair:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;00100000:10000000:9.0:1582907058.066997:0:26150:0:(lfsck_striped_dir.c:2190:lfsck_namespace_striped_dir_rescan()) snx11281-MDT0001-osd: namespace LFSCK repair the shard 0 [0x24010cce0:0x376a:0x0] of the striped directory [0x24010ce0d:0x15cd0:0x0] with dangling no/no, rename no/no, llinkea no/no, repair_lmvea no/no: rc = 0

00100000:10000000:9.0:1582907058.067116:0:26150:0:(lfsck_striped_dir.c:2190:lfsck_namespace_striped_dir_rescan()) snx11281-MDT0001-osd: namespace LFSCK repair the shard 1 [0x2000ecd29:0x376b:0x0] of the striped directory [0x24010ce0d:0x15cd0:0x0] with dangling no/no, rename no/no, llinkea no/no, repair_lmvea no/no: rc = 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;dangling no/no, rename no/no, llinkea no/no, repair_lmvea no/no&quot; indicates there were no errors, so why those messages populate the lustre debug log?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
